div.p:
But the Greek word (
                  〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
               ) moſt properly ſignifies: How ſhall he not: &c. This thwarts not the other two, but (according to the manner of expreſſion, a queſtion carrying it's anſwer in it: which is, He ſhall with him freely give us all things) renders the text as a gracious promiſe of continuing the Fathers bounty to the Saints, begun in them at their houre of converſion.
